backend.description: By default, operate against AWS.  Set to 'localstack' to use against a local localstack instance.  This is primarily intended for debugging.

default_key_expiry.description: Default maximum age of a key before the key is scheduled for deletion

default_key_grace.description: Default age at which we gracefully attempt to rotate out the key

active_key_id.description: Active AWS Access Key ID to be utilized by clients

active_key_secret.description: Active AWS Access Key Secret to be utilized by clients

user_name.description: IAM name of the user to maintain active keys against

block.description: Manages a user's AWS access keys, attempting to gracefully rotate out aged keys while keeping an active key.
